===Etymology===
{{ME.}} {{term|lang=enm|how}}, {{term|hou}}, {{term|hu}}, {{term|hwu}}, {{OE.}} {{term|hu|lang=ang|hū}}, from the same root as {{term|hwæt||who, what}}; akin to Old Saxon {{term|hww}}, Dutch {{term|hoe}}, compare German {{term|wie||how}}. See {{term|who}} and compare {{term|why}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/haʊ/}}, {{SAMPA|/haU/}}
* {{audio|en-us-how.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*: {{rhymes|aʊ}}

===Adverb===
{{en-adv|-}}

# To [[what]] [[degree]].
#: '''''How''' often do you practice?''
# In what [[state]].
#: '''''How''' are you?''
#: '''''How''' was your vacation?''
# In what [[manner]].
#: '''''How''' do you solve this puzzle?''
#: '''''How''' else can we get this finished?''
# {{non-gloss definitoin|Used as a modifier to indicate surprise, delight, or other strong feelings.}}
#: '''''How''' very interesting!''
#: '''''How''' wonderful it was to receive your invitation.''

